00:02:53,312 --> 00:02:55,521
Good guess. But wrong.

5
00:03:05,074 --> 00:03:06,824
Clear your head.

6
00:03:08,912 --> 00:03:12,205
All right. Tell me what you think it is.

7
00:03:13,582 --> 00:03:15,167
Is it a star?

8
00:03:16,252 --> 00:03:20,004
It is a star. Very good. That's great.

9
00:03:20,173 --> 00:03:22,925
Okay. All right.

10
00:03:23,675 --> 00:03:27,094
Think hard. What is it?

11
00:03:27,889 --> 00:03:29,764
Circle.

12
00:03:29,932 --> 00:03:33,852
Close. But definitely wrong.

13
00:03:36,021 --> 00:03:37,647
Okay.

14
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:41,567
- All right. Ready? - Yeah.

15
00:03:41,735 --> 00:03:43,110
All right.

16
00:03:44,781 --> 00:03:46,448
What is it?

17
00:03:48,825 --> 00:03:50,159
Come on.

18
00:03:51,454 --> 00:03:53,288
Figure eight.

19
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:59,545
Incredible. That's 5 for 5. You can't see these, can you?

20
00:03:59,711 --> 00:04:03,674
- You're not cheating me, are you? - No, I swear they're just coming to me.

21
00:04:04,509 --> 00:04:05,967
Okay.

22
00:04:06,969 --> 00:04:11,598
- Nervous? - Yes. I don't like this.

23
00:04:11,765 --> 00:04:17,019
You only have 75 more to go, okay? What's this one?

24
00:04:20,524 --> 00:04:22,526
It's a couple of wavy lines.

25
00:04:22,694 --> 00:04:26,487
- Sorry. This isn't your lucky day. - I know.

26
00:04:29,242 --> 00:04:31,076
Wait...

27
00:04:34,831 --> 00:04:36,540
I'm getting a little tired of this!

28
00:04:36,707 --> 00:04:39,209
You volunteered, didn't you? We're paying, aren't we?

29
00:04:39,377 --> 00:04:42,629
Yeah, but I didn't know you were gonna give me electric shocks!

30
00:04:42,797 --> 00:04:44,840
What are you trying to prove here, anyway?

31
00:04:45,007 --> 00:04:48,968
I'm studying the effect of negative reinforcement on ESP ability.

32
00:04:49,137 --> 00:04:52,598
The effect? I'll tell you what the effect is. It's pissing me off!

33
00:04:52,764 --> 00:04:54,600
Well, then maybe my theory is correct!

34
00:04:54,766 --> 00:04:58,562
- You can keep the 5 bucks. I've had it. - I will, mister!

35
00:05:02,524 --> 00:05:05,235
You may as well get used to that.

36
00:05:05,485 --> 00:05:10,156
It's the kind of resentment that your ability will provoke in some people.

37
00:05:10,490 --> 00:05:13,576
Do you think I have it, Dr. Venkman?

38
00:05:14,911 --> 00:05:17,372
You're no fluke, Jennifer.

39
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:20,000
This is it. This is definitely it!

40
00:05:20,168 --> 00:05:22,543
Did those UV lenses come in for the video camera?

41
00:05:22,711 --> 00:05:26,255
And that blank tape, I need it, the one you erased yesterday.

42
00:05:26,423 --> 00:05:29,550
- Will you excuse me for a second? - Sure.

43
00:05:30,887 --> 00:05:34,221
I'm right in the middle of something, Ray.

44
00:05:34,389 --> 00:05:36,057
I need more time with this subject.

45
00:05:36,225 --> 00:05:38,726
Could you come back in an hour, hour and a half?

46
00:05:38,894 --> 00:05:40,896
Peter, at 1:40 p. M...

47
00:05:41,064 --> 00:05:44,483
...at the main branch of The New York Public Library on Fifth Avenue...

48
00:05:44,651 --> 00:05:49,362
...10 people witnessed a free-floating, full-torso, vaporous apparition.

49
00:05:49,529 --> 00:05:51,697
It blew books off shelves from 20 feet away...

50
00:05:51,865 --> 00:05:54,242
...and scared the socks off some poor librarian.

51
00:05:54,409 --> 00:05:56,620
I'm very excited. I'm very pleased.

52
00:05:56,788 --> 00:06:00,706
I want you to get right down there, check it out, and get back to me.

53
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:03,709
You're coming with us on this one. Spengler went down there.

54
00:06:03,877 --> 00:06:06,922
He took PKE valences, went right off the top of the scale.

55
00:06:07,089 --> 00:06:11,425
Buried the needle. We're close on this one. I can feel it.

56
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:18,016
I can feel it. We're very, very close.

57
00:06:19,976 --> 00:06:23,230
I have to go now, Jennifer, but I'd like to work with you some more.

58
00:06:23,398 --> 00:06:25,564
Perhaps you could come back this evening at...?

59
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:27,108
Eight o'clock?

60
00:06:27,276 --> 00:06:32,154
I was just going to say, "8:00?" You are a legitimate phenomenon.

61
00:06:35,201 --> 00:06:36,534
As a friend, I must say...

62
00:06:36,702 --> 00:06:39,663
...you've finally gone around the bend on this ghost business.

63
00:06:39,831 --> 00:06:42,832
You guys have been meeting every schizo in the five boroughs...

64
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,002
...who says he has a paranormal experience. What have you seen?

65
00:06:46,545 --> 00:06:51,507
You forget, I was there at an undersea, unexplained mass sponge migration.

66
00:06:51,675 --> 00:06:56,555
Oh, Ray, the sponges migrated about a foot and a half.

67
00:07:02,519 --> 00:07:04,478
- You're here. - Yeah, what have you got?

68
00:07:04,646 --> 00:07:07,858
This is big, this is very big. There's definitely something here.

69
00:07:08,024 --> 00:07:11,778
Egon, this reminds me of the time you tried to drill a hole through your head.

70
00:07:11,946 --> 00:07:13,988
- Remember that? - That would've worked if...

71
00:07:14,156 --> 00:07:17,074
I'm Roger Delacorte. Are you the men from the university?

72
00:07:17,242 --> 00:07:20,829
Yes. I'm Dr. Venkman. Dr. Stantz. Egon.

73
00:07:20,997 --> 00:07:25,000
Thank you for coming. I hope we can clear this up quickly and quietly.

74
00:07:25,168 --> 00:07:29,504
Let's not rush things. We don't even know what you have yet.

75
00:07:30,213 --> 00:07:32,007
I don't remember seeing any legs...

76
00:07:32,175 --> 00:07:35,343
...but it definitely had arms, because it reached out for me.

77
00:07:35,511 --> 00:07:37,637
Arms? I can't wait to get a look at this.

78
00:07:37,805 --> 00:07:40,598
Alice, I'll ask you a couple of standard questions, okay?

79
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,100
Have you or any member of your family...

80
00:07:43,269 --> 00:07:47,355
...ever been diagnosed schizophrenic, mentally incompetent?

81
00:07:48,191 --> 00:07:51,276
My uncle thought he was St. Jerome.

82
00:07:52,444 --> 00:07:55,237
I'd call that a big yes.

83
00:07:56,281 --> 00:07:59,701
Are you habitually using drugs, stimulants, alcohol?

84
00:07:59,869 --> 00:08:03,163
- No. - No, no. Just asking.

85
00:08:03,538 --> 00:08:06,833
Are you, Alice, menstruating right now?

86
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:12,172
- What has that got to do with it? - Back off, man. I'm a scientist.

87
00:08:12,423 --> 00:08:15,466
Ray, it's moving. Come on.

88
00:08:40,534 --> 00:08:41,951
Look!

89
00:08:47,582 --> 00:08:51,418
- This is hot, Ray. - Symmetrical book-stacking.

90
00:08:51,586 --> 00:08:55,506
Just like the Philadelphia mass turbulence of 1947.

91
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:59,927
You're right. No human being would stack books like this.

92
00:09:00,428 --> 00:09:04,014
Listen! Do you smell something?

93
00:09:11,816 --> 00:09:15,610
Talk about telekinetic activity. Look at this mess.

94
00:09:16,528 --> 00:09:18,822
Raymond, look at this.

95
00:09:19,322 --> 00:09:21,533
Ectoplasmic residue.

96
00:09:21,701 --> 00:09:25,787
- Venkman, get a sample of this. - It's the real thing.

97
00:09:25,955 --> 00:09:28,289
Somebody blows their nose, and you wanna keep it?

98
00:09:28,456 --> 00:09:30,125
I'd like to analyze it.

99
00:09:30,293 --> 00:09:34,254
- There's more over here. - I'm getting stronger readings here.

100
00:09:40,302 --> 00:09:42,095
This way.

101
00:09:43,972 --> 00:09:45,599
Come on.

102
00:09:55,484 --> 00:09:57,818
Egon, your mucus.

103
00:10:05,119 --> 00:10:07,162
This happen to you before?

104
00:10:09,081 --> 00:10:10,664
First time?

105
00:10:36,024 --> 00:10:37,775
It's here.

106
00:10:38,693 --> 00:10:42,905
A full torso apparition. And it's real.

107
00:10:47,662 --> 00:10:49,578
So, what do we do?

108
00:10:54,376 --> 00:10:57,504
Could you come over here and talk to me for a second, please?

109
00:10:57,672 --> 00:10:59,838
Could you just come here for a second, please?

110
00:11:00,006 --> 00:11:03,467
Right over here. Come here, Francine. Come here.

111
00:11:04,052 --> 00:11:07,138
- What do we do? - I don't know. What do you think?

112
00:11:07,306 --> 00:11:09,099
Stop that!

113
00:11:09,392 --> 00:11:12,559
We've gotta make contact. One of us should try to speak to it.

114
00:11:12,727 --> 00:11:14,187
Good idea.

115
00:11:22,904 --> 00:11:24,405
Hello.

116
00:11:24,948 --> 00:11:26,615
I'm Peter.

117
00:11:27,451 --> 00:11:30,745
Where are you from? Originally.

118
00:11:35,418 --> 00:11:38,628
All right. Okay. The usual stuff isn't working.

119
00:11:38,796 --> 00:11:43,133
Okay, I have a plan. I know exactly what to do.

120
00:11:45,094 --> 00:11:47,220
Now, stay close.

121
00:11:47,554 --> 00:11:49,596
Stay close.

122
00:11:49,849 --> 00:11:52,767
I know. Do exactly as I say.

123
00:11:52,934 --> 00:11:55,186
Get ready. Ready?

124
00:11:55,354 --> 00:11:56,855
Get her!

125
00:12:05,364 --> 00:12:08,450
- Did you see it? What was it? - We'll get back to you.

126
00:12:08,616 --> 00:12:09,951
Wait!

127
00:12:18,878 --> 00:12:23,338
"Get her." That was your whole plan. Get her.

128
00:12:24,383 --> 00:12:28,302
- It was scientific. - I just got overexcited.

129
00:12:28,471 --> 00:12:32,474
But wasn't it incredible, Pete? We actually touched the etheric plane.

130
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,725
You know what this could mean to the school?

131
00:12:34,894 --> 00:12:37,227
Yeah, it's gonna be bigger than the microchip.

132
00:12:37,395 --> 00:12:39,105
The experience wasn't wasted.

133
00:12:39,273 --> 00:12:42,107
According to these readings, we have an excellent chance...

134
00:12:42,275 --> 00:12:43,942
...of catching and holding a ghost.

135
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:48,114
This is great. If the ionization rate is constant for all ectoplasmic entities...

136
00:12:48,282 --> 00:12:51,493
...we could really bust some heads. In a spiritual sense, of course.

137
00:12:51,659 --> 00:12:54,662
Spengs, you serious about this catching a ghost?

138
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:56,748
I'm always serious.

139
00:12:57,290 --> 00:13:00,960
Egon, I'm gonna take back some of the things I've said about you.

140
00:13:03,923 --> 00:13:05,590
You've earned it.

141
00:13:07,676 --> 00:13:11,804
The possibilities are limitless. Hey, Dean Yeager.

142
00:13:15,350 --> 00:13:17,936
I trust you're moving us to better quarters on campus.

143
00:13:18,104 --> 00:13:20,187
No, you're being moved off campus.

144
00:13:20,355 --> 00:13:23,024
The Board of Regents has decided to terminate your grant.

145
00:13:23,192 --> 00:13:26,027
You are to vacate these premises immediately.

146
00:13:26,195 --> 00:13:29,197
This is preposterous. I demand an explanation.

147
00:13:29,365 --> 00:13:32,366
Fine. This university will no longer continue...

148
00:13:32,534 --> 00:13:35,870
...any funding of any kind for your group's activities.

149
00:13:36,038 --> 00:13:37,705
But the kids love us.

150
00:13:37,873 --> 00:13:44,003
Dr. Venkman, we believe the purpose of science is to serve mankind.

151
00:13:44,171 --> 00:13:48,716
You, however, seem to regard science as some kind of dodge or hustle.

152
00:13:48,926 --> 00:13:51,302
Your theories are the worst kind of popular tripe.

153
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:54,806
Your methods are sloppy, and your conclusions are highly questionable.

154
00:13:54,974 --> 00:13:58,433
You are a poor scientist, Dr. Venkman.

155
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:01,062
I see.

156
00:14:01,230 --> 00:14:06,067
And you have no place in this department or in this university.

157
00:14:06,568 --> 00:14:09,486
This is a major disgrace. Forget MIT or Stanford now.

158
00:14:09,654 --> 00:14:12,072
They wouldn't touch us with a 10-meter cattle prod.

159
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,576
You're always so concerned about your reputation.

160
00:14:14,743 --> 00:14:17,578
Einstein did his best stuff when he was a patent clerk.

161
00:14:17,745 --> 00:14:19,581
You know how much a patent clerk earns?

162
00:14:19,748 --> 00:14:23,418
The university gave us money. We didn't have to produce anything.

163
00:14:23,586 --> 00:14:26,671
You've never been out of college. You don't know what it's like.

164
00:14:26,838 --> 00:14:30,258
I've worked in the private sector. They expect results.

165
00:14:30,426 --> 00:14:32,259
For whatever reasons, Ray...

166
00:14:32,469 --> 00:14:37,514
...call it fate, call it luck, call it karma...

167
00:14:37,682 --> 00:14:40,518
...I believe that everything happens for a reason.

168
00:14:40,686 --> 00:14:44,772
I believe that we were destined to get thrown out of this dump.

169
00:14:44,981 --> 00:14:49,943
- For what purpose? - To go into business for ourselves.

170
00:14:53,908 --> 00:14:56,743
This ecto-containment system Spengler and I have in mind...

171
00:14:56,911 --> 00:15:00,455
...will require a load of capital. Where will we get the money?

172
00:15:02,124 --> 00:15:05,793
I don't know. I don't know.

173
00:15:07,796 --> 00:15:10,048
You're never gonna regret this, Ray.

174
00:15:10,216 --> 00:15:12,799
My parents left me that house. I was born there.

175
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:16,221
You won't lose the house. Everybody has three mortgages nowadays.

176
00:15:16,388 --> 00:15:19,057
But at 19 percent? You didn't even bargain with the guy.

177
00:15:19,225 --> 00:15:21,725
Ray, for your information, the interest rate alone...

178
00:15:21,894 --> 00:15:24,645
...for the first five years comes to 95,000 dollars.

179
00:15:24,812 --> 00:15:27,815
Will you guys relax? We are on the threshold of establishing...

180
00:15:28,024 --> 00:15:31,068
...the indispensable defense science of the next decade:

181
00:15:31,236 --> 00:15:34,822
Professional paranormal investigations and eliminations.

182
00:15:35,032 --> 00:15:39,661
The franchise rights alone will make us rich beyond our wildest dreams.

183
00:15:39,827 --> 00:15:42,996
There's office space, sleeping quarters and showers...

184
00:15:43,164 --> 00:15:44,749
...and there's a full kitchen.

185
00:15:44,917 --> 00:15:49,836
It just seems a little pricey for a unique fixer-upper opportunity, that's all.

186
00:15:50,047 --> 00:15:51,838
What do you think, Egon?

187
00:15:52,048 --> 00:15:54,259
I think this building should be condemned.

188
00:15:54,426 --> 00:15:56,970
There's metal fatigue in all the load-bearing members.

189
00:15:57,136 --> 00:16:00,764
The wiring is substandard. It's inadequate for our power needs.

190
00:16:00,932 --> 00:16:03,850
And the neighborhood is like a demilitarized zone.

191
00:16:04,019 --> 00:16:06,937
Hey, does this pole still work?

192
00:16:09,692 --> 00:16:14,028
Wow, this place is great. When can we move in?

193
00:16:14,196 --> 00:16:18,198
You gotta try this pole. I'm gonna get my stuff.

194
00:16:21,577 --> 00:16:26,581
Hey, we should stay here tonight, sleep here. You know, to try it out.

195
00:16:36,342 --> 00:16:38,552
- I think we'll take it. - Good.

196
00:17:13,338 --> 00:17:14,672
Hi.

197
00:17:20,261 --> 00:17:22,680
- Dana, it's you. - Hi. Yes, Louis, it's me.

198
00:17:22,847 --> 00:17:25,223
- I thought it was the drugstore. - Are you sick?

199
00:17:25,392 --> 00:17:27,101
No, I'm fine. I feel great.

200
00:17:27,269 --> 00:17:30,438
Just ordered some more vitamins and stuff. I was just exercising.

201
00:17:30,605 --> 00:17:33,273
I taped 20-Minute Workout and played it at high speed...

202
00:17:33,442 --> 00:17:35,609
...so it took 10 minutes. Got a great workout.

203
00:17:35,778 --> 00:17:37,528
Want to come in for a mineral water?

204
00:17:37,695 --> 00:17:40,948
I'd really like to, Louis, but I have a rehearsal. Excuse me.

205
00:17:41,157 --> 00:17:43,284
No sweat. I'll take a rain check on that.

206
00:17:43,451 --> 00:17:46,913
I have plenty of low-sodium mineral water and other nutritious foods.

207
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,955
- But you already know that. - I know that.

208
00:17:49,165 --> 00:17:52,210
That reminds me, I'm having a big party for all my clients.

209
00:17:52,377 --> 00:17:54,211
My fourth anniversary as an accountant.

210
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:56,297
Even though you do your own tax return...

211
00:17:56,464 --> 00:17:58,257
...stop by, since you're my neighbor.

212
00:17:58,424 --> 00:18:00,550
Thank you, Louis. I'll really try to stop by.

213
00:18:00,803 --> 00:18:03,887
You shouldn't leave your TV on so loud when you go out.

214
00:18:04,056 --> 00:18:06,057
The creep down the hall phoned the manager.

215
00:18:06,224 --> 00:18:08,393
That's strange. I didn't realize I left it on.

216
00:18:08,559 --> 00:18:11,395
I climbed on the ledge and tried to disconnect the cable...

217
00:18:11,563 --> 00:18:14,981
...but I couldn't get in, so I turned up my TV real loud too...

218
00:18:15,192 --> 00:18:18,486
...so everyone would think both our TVs had something wrong with them.

219
00:18:18,694 --> 00:18:22,240
Okay, so I'll see you later, huh? I'll give you a call.

220
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,492
I gotta have a shower.

221
00:18:29,498 --> 00:18:32,666
Are you troubled by strange noises in the middle of the night?

222
00:18:32,835 --> 00:18:36,002
Do you experience feelings of dread in your basement or attic?

223
00:18:36,171 --> 00:18:39,423
Have you or any of your family ever seen a spook, specter or ghost?

224
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:43,176
If the answer is yes, pick up your phone and call the professionals.

225
00:18:43,345 --> 00:18:44,846
Ghostbusters.

226
00:18:45,012 --> 00:18:47,347
Our courteous staff is on call 24 hours a day...

227
00:18:47,516 --> 00:18:49,808
...to serve your supernatural-elimination needs.

228
00:18:49,977 --> 00:18:53,145
We're ready to believe you.

229
00:20:04,675 --> 00:20:06,426
Zuul.

230
00:20:10,891 --> 00:20:12,432
You don't think it's too subtle?

231
00:20:12,601 --> 00:20:16,229
You don't think people are gonna drive down and not see the sign?

232
00:20:24,238 --> 00:20:26,696
You can't park that here!

233
00:20:30,786 --> 00:20:32,953
Everybody can relax, I found the car.

234
00:20:33,121 --> 00:20:35,580
Needs some suspension work and shocks...

235
00:20:35,749 --> 00:20:39,794
...and brakes, brake pads, linings, steering box, transmission, rear end.

236
00:20:39,961 --> 00:20:41,461
- How much? - Only 4800.

237
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:44,298
Maybe new rings, also mufflers, a little wiring.

238
00:20:48,886 --> 00:20:50,971
- Janine, any calls? - No.

239
00:20:51,138 --> 00:20:53,641
- Any messages? - No.

240
00:20:54,643 --> 00:20:57,979
- Any customers? - No, Dr. Venkman.

241
00:20:59,439 --> 00:21:01,398
It's a good job, isn't it?

242
00:21:01,983 --> 00:21:04,986
Type something, will you? We're paying for this stuff.

243
00:21:05,153 --> 00:21:08,489
Don't stare at me. You've got the bug eyes.

244
00:21:09,156 --> 00:21:10,825
Janine?

245
00:21:10,992 --> 00:21:14,119
Sorry about the "bug eyes" thing. I'll be in my office.

246
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:20,125
You're very handy. I can tell.

247
00:21:21,711 --> 00:21:26,007
- I bet you like to read a lot too. - Print is dead.

248
00:21:26,424 --> 00:21:30,010
Oh, that's very fascinating to me. I read a lot myself.

249
00:21:30,178 --> 00:21:34,848
Some people think I'm too intellectual, but it's a fabulous way to spend time.

250
00:21:35,017 --> 00:21:39,144
I also play racquetball. Do you have any hobbies?

251
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:43,231
I collect spores, molds and fungus.

252
00:21:48,195 --> 00:21:49,529
Hello?

253
00:22:07,548 --> 00:22:10,759
Excuse me. Is this...? This is the Ghostbusters' office.

254
00:22:10,969 --> 00:22:13,887
Yes, it is. Can I help you?

255
00:22:14,056 --> 00:22:17,974
I don't have an appointment. I'd like to talk to someone, please.

256
00:22:19,603 --> 00:22:23,271
I'm Peter Venkman. May I help you?

257
00:22:23,481 --> 00:22:28,778
Well, I don't know. What I have to say may sound a little unusual.

258
00:22:28,987 --> 00:22:31,780
That's all we get, day in, day out, around this place.

259
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:35,451
- Come into my office, Miss... - Barrett. Dana Barrett.

260
00:22:35,618 --> 00:22:39,913
And this voice said, "Zuul," and then I slammed the refrigerator door and left.

261
00:22:40,082 --> 00:22:43,125
That was two days ago, and I haven't been back to my apartment.

262
00:22:43,292 --> 00:22:46,461
Generally, you don't see that behavior in a major appliance.

263
00:22:46,630 --> 00:22:47,962
What do you think it was?

264
00:22:48,131 --> 00:22:50,590
Well, if I knew what it was, I wouldn't be here.

265
00:22:50,759 --> 00:22:52,300
Egon, what do you think?

266
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:55,596
She's telling the truth. At least she thinks she is.

267
00:22:55,931 --> 00:23:00,267
Well, of course I'm telling the truth. Who would make up a story like that?

268
00:23:00,434 --> 00:23:02,310
Some are people who just want attention.

269
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:04,605
Others are nutballs who come off the street.

270
00:23:04,772 --> 00:23:09,151
You know what it could be? Past life experience intruding on present time.

271
00:23:09,318 --> 00:23:11,945
Could be a memory stored in the collective unconscious.

272
00:23:12,114 --> 00:23:15,156
I wouldn't rule out clairvoyance or telepathic contact either.

273
00:23:15,325 --> 00:23:17,910
I'm sorry, I don't believe in any of those things.

274
00:23:18,077 --> 00:23:22,288
Well, that's all right. I don't either. But there are some things we do...

275
00:23:22,457 --> 00:23:26,000
...standard procedures in a case like this, which often bring us results.

276
00:23:26,169 --> 00:23:29,255
I could check out the structural details in the building.

277
00:23:29,423 --> 00:23:32,007
Maybe the building has a history of psychic turbulence.

278
00:23:32,174 --> 00:23:33,509
Right. Good idea.

279
00:23:33,676 --> 00:23:35,845
I could search "Zuul" in the usual literature.

280
00:23:36,054 --> 00:23:38,513
- Spates Catalog. - Tobin's Spirit Guide.

281
00:23:38,682 --> 00:23:42,643
I'll take Miss Barrett back to her apartment and check her out.

282
00:23:42,810 --> 00:23:46,814
I'll go check out Miss Barrett's apartment. Okay?

283
00:23:47,356 --> 00:23:49,191
Okay.

284
00:23:49,984 --> 00:23:52,819
- Thank you. - It's okay.

285
00:24:00,578 --> 00:24:01,996
Please, let me.

286
00:24:02,163 --> 00:24:06,375
If something's gonna happen here, I want it to happen to me first.

287
00:24:10,672 --> 00:24:12,714
That's the closet.

288
00:24:19,638 --> 00:24:21,515
They hate this.

289
00:24:22,308 --> 00:24:24,018
I like to torture them.

290
00:24:24,185 --> 00:24:28,021
That's right, boys. It's Dr. Venkman!

291
00:24:33,653 --> 00:24:35,695
It's a lot of space.

292
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:39,741
- Just you? - Yes.

293
00:24:40,326 --> 00:24:41,701
Good.

294
00:24:45,874 --> 00:24:48,250
What is that thing you're doing?

295
00:24:49,001 --> 00:24:52,212
It's technical. It's one of our little toys.

296
00:24:52,380 --> 00:24:53,923
I see.

297
00:24:56,134 --> 00:25:00,054
That's the bedroom. But nothing ever happened in there.

298
00:25:03,016 --> 00:25:05,142
What a crime.

299
00:25:07,061 --> 00:25:10,064
You know, you don't act like a scientist.

300
00:25:10,231 --> 00:25:15,068
- They're usually pretty stiff. - You're more like a game-show host.

301
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:23,661
That's the kitchen, huh?

302
00:25:35,965 --> 00:25:38,049
- Dana, are these the eggs? - Yes.

303
00:25:38,218 --> 00:25:41,386
I was over there, and these eggs jumped out of their shells...

304
00:25:41,555 --> 00:25:44,138
...and started to cook on the counter. - That is weird.

305
00:25:44,307 --> 00:25:48,434
That's when I started to hear that awful noise coming from the refrigerator.

306
00:25:49,479 --> 00:25:53,941
You've come all this way. Would you like to check the refrigerator?

307
00:25:55,402 --> 00:25:58,778
Better check the fridge. Good call.

308
00:26:03,826 --> 00:26:06,202
Oh, my God.

309
00:26:06,704 --> 00:26:09,248
Look at all the junk food.

310
00:26:09,415 --> 00:26:12,292
- No. Goddamn it! This wasn't... - You actually eat this stuff?

311
00:26:12,460 --> 00:26:14,336
This wasn't here. There was nothing here.

312
00:26:14,503 --> 00:26:18,132
There was a space and a building with flames coming out of it.

313
00:26:18,299 --> 00:26:22,010
There were creatures writhing around, and they were growling and snarling.

314
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:24,971
And there were flames, and I heard a voice say, "Zuul."

315
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,472
It was right here.

316
00:26:26,641 --> 00:26:28,474
I'm sorry, I'm not getting any reading.

317
00:26:28,643 --> 00:26:31,686
Well, are you sure you're using that thing correctly?

318
00:26:31,855 --> 00:26:35,857
I think so. But I'm sure there are no animals in there.

319
00:26:36,026 --> 00:26:37,358
Well, that's great.

320
00:26:37,527 --> 00:26:41,113
Either I have a monster in my kitchen, or I'm completely crazy.

321
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:43,615
I don't think you're crazy.

322
00:26:44,116 --> 00:26:49,329
Oh, good. That makes me feel so much better.

323
00:26:49,497 --> 00:26:51,164
Let me tell you something about me.

324
00:26:51,333 --> 00:26:54,460
I come home from work to my place, and all I have is my work.

325
00:26:54,627 --> 00:26:56,170
There's nothing else in my life.

326
00:26:56,337 --> 00:27:00,633
I meet you and say, "There's someone with the same problem I have."

327
00:27:00,799 --> 00:27:03,635
Yes, we both have the same problem. You.

328
00:27:07,348 --> 00:27:09,516
I'm gonna go for broke.

329
00:27:12,186 --> 00:27:15,064
- I am madly in love with you. - I don't believe this.

330
00:27:15,272 --> 00:27:17,816
Will you please leave?

331
00:27:18,067 --> 00:27:21,362
And then she threw me out of her life. She thought I was a creep.

332
00:27:21,528 --> 00:27:24,530
She thought I was a geek, and she probably wasn't the first.

333
00:27:24,699 --> 00:27:26,991
You are so odd.

334
00:27:30,913 --> 00:27:33,374
- No. - I've got it!

335
00:27:33,540 --> 00:27:36,335
- No. - I'll prove myself to you.

336
00:27:36,502 --> 00:27:38,252
That's not necessary.

337
00:27:38,421 --> 00:27:41,214
- Yeah, I'll solve your little problem. - Okay.

338
00:27:41,383 --> 00:27:45,051
And then you'll say, "Pete Venkman's a guy who can get things done.

339
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:47,221
- I wonder what makes him tick." - I wonder.

340
00:27:47,388 --> 00:27:50,391
"I wonder if he'd be interested in knowing what makes me tick."

341
00:27:50,557 --> 00:27:53,352
I'll bet you're gonna be thinking about me after I'm gone.

342
00:27:53,519 --> 00:27:54,936
I bet I am.

343
00:27:56,439 --> 00:27:58,106
No kiss?

344
00:28:08,117 --> 00:28:10,076
To our first customer.

345
00:28:10,244 --> 00:28:13,372
To our first and only customer.

346
00:28:14,624 --> 00:28:16,290
I'll need to draw some petty cash.

347
00:28:16,459 --> 00:28:19,294
I should take her out to dinner. We don't want to lose her.

348
00:28:19,503 --> 00:28:24,590
This magnificent feast here represents the last of the petty cash.

349
00:28:26,301 --> 00:28:28,929
Hey, slow down. Chew your food.

350
00:28:30,181 --> 00:28:32,516
Hello, Ghostbusters.

351
00:28:33,101 --> 00:28:35,978
Yes, of course they're serious.

352
00:28:37,939 --> 00:28:39,480
You do?

353
00:28:40,107 --> 00:28:42,026
You have?

354
00:28:42,192 --> 00:28:43,943
No kidding.

355
00:28:44,695 --> 00:28:47,990
Well, just give me the address.

356
00:28:48,615 --> 00:28:52,911
Yes, of course. Oh, they'll be totally discreet.

357
00:28:53,788 --> 00:28:55,705
Thank you.

358
00:28:56,124 --> 00:28:58,125
We got one!

359
00:29:03,006 --> 00:29:04,714
It's a call!

360
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:13,848
Come on!

361
00:29:48,509 --> 00:29:50,760
Hey, anybody see a ghost?

362
00:29:55,682 --> 00:29:58,059
- Thank you for coming so quickly. - Jesus!

363
00:29:58,228 --> 00:30:01,270
The guests are asking questions, and I'm running out of excuses.

364
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:02,772
Has it happened before?

365
00:30:02,981 --> 00:30:05,526
Most of the original staff knows about the 12th floor.

366
00:30:05,692 --> 00:30:07,193
- The disturbances, I mean. - Yeah.

367
00:30:07,362 --> 00:30:10,279
But it's been quiet for years up until two weeks ago.

368
00:30:10,490 --> 00:30:12,240
It was never, ever this bad, though.

369
00:30:12,407 --> 00:30:16,452
- Did you ever report it to anyone? - No. Heavens, no.

370
00:30:16,621 --> 00:30:19,248
The owners don't like us to even talk about it.

371
00:30:19,414 --> 00:30:21,415
I hope we could take care of this quietly.

372
00:30:21,584 --> 00:30:22,917
- It's done. - Tonight.

373
00:30:23,086 --> 00:30:24,627
Yes, sir. Don't worry.

374
00:30:24,796 --> 00:30:27,381
We handle this kind of thing all the time.

375
00:30:35,557 --> 00:30:38,892
What are you supposed to be, some kind of a cosmonaut?

376
00:30:39,059 --> 00:30:42,938
No, we're exterminators. Somebody saw a cockroach up on 12th.

377
00:30:43,105 --> 00:30:47,526
- That's gotta be some cockroach. - Bite your head off, man.

378
00:30:51,239 --> 00:30:54,825
- Going up? - I'll take the next one.

379
00:30:57,412 --> 00:31:01,289
It just occurred to me we haven't had a successful test of this equipment.

380
00:31:01,457 --> 00:31:03,666
- I blame myself. - So do I.

381
00:31:03,835 --> 00:31:06,836
- Well, no sense worrying about it now. - Why worry?

382
00:31:07,046 --> 00:31:11,592
Each of us is wearing an unlicensed nuclear accelerator on his back.

383
00:31:11,759 --> 00:31:16,180
Yep. Well, let's get ready. Switch me on.

384
00:31:52,217 --> 00:31:54,884
What the hell are you doing?

385
00:31:56,346 --> 00:31:58,555
- Sorry. - I'm sorry.

386
00:31:58,722 --> 00:32:00,807
We thought you were someone else.

387
00:32:03,144 --> 00:32:05,103
Successful test.

388
00:32:05,520 --> 00:32:07,230
I guess so.

389
00:32:07,731 --> 00:32:09,857
- I think we'd better split up. - Good idea.

390
00:32:10,026 --> 00:32:11,984
Yeah, we can do more damage that way.

391
00:32:40,265 --> 00:32:42,766
Venkman? Venkman!

392
00:32:50,525 --> 00:32:52,858
Disgusting blob.

393
00:32:53,653 --> 00:32:55,945
I'm gonna have to hold him myself.

394
00:33:37,488 --> 00:33:39,280
Come in, Ray.

395
00:33:40,950 --> 00:33:43,826
Venkman! I saw it! I saw it!

396
00:33:44,202 --> 00:33:45,996
It's right here, Ray.

397
00:33:46,204 --> 00:33:47,748
It's looking at me.

398
00:33:47,914 --> 00:33:49,833
He's an ugly little spud, isn't he?

399
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,500
I think he can hear you, Ray.

400
00:33:51,711 --> 00:33:53,586
Don't move. It won't hurt you.

401
00:34:01,304 --> 00:34:03,137
Venkman!

402
00:34:04,973 --> 00:34:07,601
Venkman! Pete!

403
00:34:10,228 --> 00:34:12,271
Venkman, what happened? Are you okay?

404
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:13,856
He slimed me.

405
00:34:14,025 --> 00:34:17,443
That's great! Actual physical contact!

406
00:34:17,612 --> 00:34:19,780
- Can you move? - Ray. Ray! Come in, please!

407
00:34:19,947 --> 00:34:21,280
I feel so funky.

408
00:34:21,449 --> 00:34:23,949
Spengler! I'm with Venkman.

409
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:25,619
He got slimed!

410
00:34:25,786 --> 00:34:27,704
That's great, Ray. Save some for me.

411
00:34:27,871 --> 00:34:30,539
Get down here, right away! It just went into a ballroom.

412
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,041
Okay, we'll be right there.

413
00:34:35,253 --> 00:34:37,630
If you and your staff could please wait out here...

414
00:34:37,798 --> 00:34:40,132
...we'll take care of everything.

415
00:34:58,568 --> 00:35:01,070
There it is. On the ceiling.

416
00:35:03,407 --> 00:35:05,826
That's the one that got me.

417
00:35:13,418 --> 00:35:14,751
All right, boys.

418
00:35:14,918 --> 00:35:16,670
Ready?

419
00:35:16,838 --> 00:35:18,170
Throw it!

420
00:35:27,806 --> 00:35:29,181
I did that. I did that.

421
00:35:29,349 --> 00:35:32,018
- That's my fault. - It's okay. The table broke the fall.

422
00:35:32,519 --> 00:35:35,021
There's something very important I forgot to tell you.

423
00:35:35,188 --> 00:35:37,523
- What? - Don't cross the streams.

424
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:40,318
- Why? - It would be bad.

425
00:35:40,610 --> 00:35:44,072
I'm fuzzy on the whole good/bad thing. What do you mean, "bad"?

426
00:35:44,239 --> 00:35:48,034
Lmagine all life as you know it stopping instantaneously and every molecule...

427
00:35:48,202 --> 00:35:50,454
...in your body exploding at the speed of light.

428
00:35:51,204 --> 00:35:52,873
Total protonic reversal.

429
00:35:53,039 --> 00:35:56,960
Right, that's bad. Okay, important safety tip. Thanks, Egon.

430
00:35:57,128 --> 00:36:01,547
All right, Ray, take the left. Egon, take the right.

431
00:36:08,097 --> 00:36:10,724
Okay, Ray, just give me one high and outside.

432
00:36:10,891 --> 00:36:12,641
Ray!

433
00:36:15,353 --> 00:36:16,771
Egon!

434
00:36:24,572 --> 00:36:26,572
Okay, all right. Hold it, hold it, hold it!

435
00:36:30,077 --> 00:36:31,619
Nice shooting, Tex!

436
00:36:31,786 --> 00:36:34,079
I assure you, there is no problem with the room.

437
00:36:34,248 --> 00:36:36,583
It'll be ready as soon as your guests are here.

438
00:36:36,751 --> 00:36:38,835
It took something out of him, but he'll move.

439
00:36:39,003 --> 00:36:41,922
I need some room to put the trap down. Give me some room.

440
00:36:42,757 --> 00:36:45,007
You'll excuse me, please.

441
00:36:51,474 --> 00:36:54,476
- Gotta get this in the clear. - Wait, wait, wait!

442
00:36:54,643 --> 00:36:57,269
I've always wanted to do this.

443
00:36:57,438 --> 00:36:58,980
And...

444
00:36:59,148 --> 00:37:02,025
- The flowers are still standing! - Okay, on my go-signal.

445
00:37:02,193 --> 00:37:05,445
Spengler, I want a confinement stream from you, okay? Go!

446
00:37:05,612 --> 00:37:08,364
Okay, hold him up there. He's gonna move. Hold him up!

447
00:37:08,532 --> 00:37:09,949
Go!

448
00:37:11,786 --> 00:37:13,619
- It's working. - Start bringing him down.

449
00:37:13,788 --> 00:37:15,539
You got him. Don't cross the stream.

450
00:37:15,706 --> 00:37:19,876
Maybe now you'll never slime a guy with a positron collider, huh?

451
00:37:20,043 --> 00:37:23,420
Venkman, shorten your stream. I don't want my face burned off.

452
00:37:23,630 --> 00:37:26,632
I'm opening the trap now. Don't look directly into the trap.

453
00:37:27,717 --> 00:37:29,385
I looked at the trap, Ray.

454
00:37:29,554 --> 00:37:33,974
Turn your streams off when I close the trap. Get ready. I'm closing it.

455
00:37:34,141 --> 00:37:36,059
Now!

456
00:37:54,579 --> 00:37:55,954
It's in there.

457
00:37:59,208 --> 00:38:01,458
Well, that wasn't such a chore, now, was it?

458
00:38:04,213 --> 00:38:06,505
Mr. Smith, quickly. I want that door open now!

459
00:38:06,673 --> 00:38:08,465
Donald, stand over there.

460
00:38:09,092 --> 00:38:11,844
We came, we saw, we kicked its ass!

461
00:38:12,012 --> 00:38:13,429
Did you see it? What is it?

462
00:38:13,597 --> 00:38:14,931
We got it.

463
00:38:15,099 --> 00:38:17,099
What is it? Will there be any more of them?

464
00:38:17,268 --> 00:38:20,186
What you had there was what we refer to as a focused...

465
00:38:20,353 --> 00:38:24,106
...non-terminal repeating phantasm, or a class-five full-roaming vapor.

466
00:38:24,275 --> 00:38:25,983
Real nasty one too.

