978
01:19:22,229 --> 01:19:24,981
Hello, everybody!

979
01:19:25,149 --> 01:19:28,485
Dr. Ray Stantz, would you please? The heart of the Ghostbusters.

980
01:19:28,653 --> 01:19:31,822
Thank you. They love you. They love you here.

981
01:19:32,407 --> 01:19:36,952
- I like that shirt, friend. - Ghostbusters! All right!

982
01:19:39,622 --> 01:19:42,750
Gotta run. Got a date with a ghost.

983
01:19:42,917 --> 01:19:45,668
Okay, whatever happens, let's be professional.

984
01:20:17,368 --> 01:20:20,371
We might have to put a little overtime in on this one.

985
01:21:15,342 --> 01:21:18,429
There they are. There they are.

986
01:21:25,186 --> 01:21:27,896
I was in no way prepared for that.

987
01:21:28,773 --> 01:21:31,774
It's all right. Don't worry. We're fine. We can handle it.

988
01:21:31,943 --> 01:21:34,278
We can take it. They want to play rough.

989
01:21:34,445 --> 01:21:38,948
Ghostbusters! Ghostbusters! Ghostbusters!

990
01:21:40,659 --> 01:21:42,243
- Wanna play rough? - Yeah.

991
01:21:42,412 --> 01:21:44,162
Let's do it.

992
01:22:09,189 --> 01:22:11,231
Where are we?

993
01:22:11,399 --> 01:22:15,485
It looks like we're in the teens somewhere.

994
01:22:15,694 --> 01:22:19,948
Well, when we get to 20, tell me. I'm gonna throw up.

995
01:22:51,523 --> 01:22:56,150
- Twenty-two. Is this it? - Yep.

996
01:23:05,036 --> 01:23:07,704
Art deco. Very nice.

997
01:23:07,872 --> 01:23:10,748
- Where is it? - It's at the end of the hall.

998
01:23:51,207 --> 01:23:53,833
Hey, where do these stairs go?

999
01:23:56,378 --> 01:23:58,046
They go up.

1000
01:24:02,761 --> 01:24:05,345
Okay, go ahead. Come on. Go ahead.

1001
01:24:06,430 --> 01:24:08,431
Watch it. Go ahead.

1002
01:24:47,721 --> 01:24:49,097
Dana.

1003
01:25:03,445 --> 01:25:07,448
Okay, so she's a dog.

1004
01:25:46,905 --> 01:25:48,614
It's a girl.

1005
01:25:53,997 --> 01:25:56,372
- It's Gozer. - I thought Gozer was a man.

1006
01:25:56,541 --> 01:26:00,377
- It's whatever it wants to be. - Whatever it is, it's gotta get by us.

1007
01:26:00,545 --> 01:26:02,045
Right.

1008
01:26:02,713 --> 01:26:04,715
Go get her, Ray!

1009
01:26:17,060 --> 01:26:19,229
Gozer the Gozerian?

1010
01:26:21,565 --> 01:26:26,653
Good evening. As a duly designated representative of the city...

1011
01:26:26,820 --> 01:26:28,529
...county and state of New York...

1012
01:26:28,698 --> 01:26:31,199
...I order you to cease all supernatural activity...

1013
01:26:31,367 --> 01:26:33,243
...and return to your place of origin...

1014
01:26:33,453 --> 01:26:36,246
...or to the nearest convenient parallel dimension.

1015
01:26:36,456 --> 01:26:39,082
That ought to do it. Thanks very much, Ray.

1016
01:26:39,250 --> 01:26:41,835
Are you a god?

1017
01:26:48,342 --> 01:26:53,764
- No. - Then die!

1018
01:27:17,622 --> 01:27:23,752
Ray, when someone asks you if you're a god, you say, "Yes."

1019
01:27:24,420 --> 01:27:29,131
All right. This chick is toast.

1020
01:27:41,436 --> 01:27:43,939
- Got your stick? - Holding it.

1021
01:27:45,984 --> 01:27:47,442
Heat them up!

1022
01:27:47,902 --> 01:27:49,319
Smoking!

1023
01:27:49,988 --> 01:27:52,823
- Make them hard. - Ready!

1024
01:27:52,990 --> 01:27:56,243
Let's show this prehistoric bitch how we do things downtown.

1025
01:27:58,829 --> 01:28:00,288
Throw it!

1026
01:28:09,172 --> 01:28:13,010
- Nimble little minx, isn't she? - We better go full stream.

1027
01:28:13,176 --> 01:28:15,470
Aim for the flattop.

1028
01:28:25,273 --> 01:28:27,024
Wasn't so hard.

1029
01:28:33,363 --> 01:28:34,864
We neutronized it.

1030
01:28:35,033 --> 01:28:37,658
You know what that means? A complete particle reversal.

1031
01:28:37,827 --> 01:28:40,662
And we had the tools. We had the talent.

1032
01:28:40,829 --> 01:28:43,122
It's Miller time.

1033
01:28:43,291 --> 01:28:47,961
- Ray, this looks extraordinarily bad. - Oh, no.

1034
01:28:48,128 --> 01:28:49,630
What?

1035
01:28:59,181 --> 01:29:00,890
Look out!

1036
01:29:23,622 --> 01:29:29,586
Sub-creatures. Gozer the Gozerian, Gozer the Destructor...

1037
01:29:29,753 --> 01:29:34,382
...Volguus Zildrohar the Traveler has come.

1038
01:29:34,550 --> 01:29:37,426
Choose and perish.

1039
01:29:37,636 --> 01:29:41,097
What do you mean, "choose"? We don't understand.

1040
01:29:41,265 --> 01:29:46,936
Choose. Choose the form of the Destructor.

1041
01:29:47,145 --> 01:29:51,733
Oh, I get it. I get it. Oh, very cute.

1042
01:29:52,275 --> 01:29:55,112
Whatever we think of. If we think of J. Edgar Hoover...

1043
01:29:55,279 --> 01:29:58,573
...J. Edgar Hoover will appear and destroy us, so empty your heads.

1044
01:29:58,740 --> 01:30:01,618
Don't think of anything. We've only got one shot at this.

1045
01:30:01,786 --> 01:30:05,622
The choice is made.

1046
01:30:05,789 --> 01:30:08,041
The Traveler has come.

1047
01:30:08,208 --> 01:30:10,292
Nobody choosed anything.

1048
01:30:10,461 --> 01:30:11,920
- Did you choose anything? - No.

1049
01:30:12,087 --> 01:30:13,421
- Did you? - My mind is blank.

1050
01:30:13,588 --> 01:30:15,966
I didn't choose anything!

1051
01:30:25,600 --> 01:30:27,476
I couldn't help it.

1052
01:30:28,479 --> 01:30:30,646
It just popped in there.

1053
01:30:31,314 --> 01:30:34,900
What? What just popped in there?

1054
01:30:35,069 --> 01:30:37,945
- I tried to think... - Look!

1055
01:30:38,905 --> 01:30:41,449
- No! It can't be. - What is it?

1056
01:30:41,617 --> 01:30:43,326
- It can't be. - What did you do, Ray?

1057
01:30:43,493 --> 01:30:45,619
Oh, shit.

1058
01:30:56,506 --> 01:30:58,591
It's the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man.

1059
01:31:30,207 --> 01:31:32,208
There's something you don't see every day.

1060
01:31:32,376 --> 01:31:34,211
I tried to think of a harmless thing.

1061
01:31:34,377 --> 01:31:36,378
Something I loved from my childhood.

1062
01:31:36,546 --> 01:31:41,384
Something that could never, ever possibly destroy us. Mr. Stay Puft.

1063
01:31:41,551 --> 01:31:43,552
Nice thinking, Ray.

1064
01:31:44,555 --> 01:31:46,555
We used to roast Stay Puft marshmallows...

1065
01:31:46,724 --> 01:31:48,557
...by the fire at Camp Waconda.

1066
01:31:50,353 --> 01:31:54,564
Ray, has gone bye-bye, Egon. What have you got left?

1067
01:31:54,899 --> 01:32:00,069
Sorry, Venkman. I'm terrified beyond the capacity for rational thought.

1068
01:32:10,081 --> 01:32:13,082
- Oh, no. - Mother pus bucket.

1069
01:32:17,838 --> 01:32:20,381
Nobody steps on a church in my town.

1070
01:32:20,550 --> 01:32:23,510
One, two, three, roast him.

1071
01:32:43,322 --> 01:32:44,948
Funny, us going out like this.

1072
01:32:45,115 --> 01:32:47,449
Killed by a 100-foot marshmallow man.

1073
01:32:47,618 --> 01:32:50,787
We've been going about this wrong. This Mr. Stay Puft is a sailor.

1074
01:32:50,954 --> 01:32:54,791
He's in New York. We get this guy laid, we won't have any trouble.

1075
01:32:58,712 --> 01:33:01,756
I have a radical idea. The door swings both ways.

1076
01:33:01,923 --> 01:33:04,426
We could reverse the particle flow through the gate.

1077
01:33:04,594 --> 01:33:06,427
How?

1078
01:33:06,595 --> 01:33:08,805
- We'll cross the streams. - Excuse me, Egon.

1079
01:33:08,972 --> 01:33:10,765
You said crossing the streams was bad.

1080
01:33:10,932 --> 01:33:14,060
- Cross the streams. - You're gonna endanger us.

1081
01:33:14,228 --> 01:33:15,979
You're gonna endanger our client...

1082
01:33:16,146 --> 01:33:19,149
...the nice lady who paid us in advance before she became a dog.

1083
01:33:19,358 --> 01:33:23,444
Not necessarily. There's definitely a very slim chance we'll survive.

1084
01:33:29,159 --> 01:33:32,912
I love this plan. I'm excited to be a part of it. Let's do it.

1085
01:33:33,079 --> 01:33:36,791
This job is definitely not worth 11,500 a year.

1086
01:33:40,421 --> 01:33:41,921
Hurry.

1087
01:33:43,882 --> 01:33:46,259
See you on the other side, Ray.

1088
01:33:48,511 --> 01:33:51,180
Nice working with you, Dr. Venkman.

1089
01:33:59,523 --> 01:34:01,190
Let's turn them on, Spengler!

1090
01:34:04,444 --> 01:34:06,695
Now, Spengler!

1091
01:34:11,993 --> 01:34:13,869
Get out of here!

1092
01:35:07,048 --> 01:35:08,550
Winston.

1093
01:35:09,510 --> 01:35:11,261
Are you all right?

1094
01:35:16,475 --> 01:35:17,934
Venkman?

1095
01:35:18,101 --> 01:35:19,435
Spengler!

1096
01:35:20,438 --> 01:35:21,938
Venkman!

1097
01:35:25,275 --> 01:35:26,775
Spengler.

1098
01:35:28,194 --> 01:35:31,030
Oh, Spengler. Oh, are you okay?

1099
01:35:31,198 --> 01:35:33,283
I feel like the floor of a taxicab.

1100
01:35:33,492 --> 01:35:35,618
- Venky! - Yeah, where are you?

1101
01:35:35,786 --> 01:35:38,121
Oh, thank God.

1102
01:35:39,247 --> 01:35:40,957
- You okay? - I'm all right.

1103
01:35:41,125 --> 01:35:42,583
- You all right? - I'm all right.

1104
01:35:42,752 --> 01:35:45,045
- You all right? - Yeah. You okay?

1105
01:35:45,212 --> 01:35:46,712
Fine.

1106
01:35:55,014 --> 01:35:57,974
It smells like barbecued dog hair.

1107
01:35:58,475 --> 01:36:00,435
Oh, Venkman.

1108
01:36:00,603 --> 01:36:02,811
Oh, Venkman, I'm sorry.

1109
01:36:03,521 --> 01:36:06,440
I'm sorry. I just... I just forgot.

1110
01:36:20,831 --> 01:36:22,414
Look!

1111
01:36:49,568 --> 01:36:52,362
Somebody turn on the lights!

1112
01:36:52,529 --> 01:36:55,657
- Help! Somebody! - Go check on that little guy.

1113
01:37:01,162 --> 01:37:03,081
What happened?

1114
01:37:12,298 --> 01:37:14,050
Where am I?

1115
01:37:15,886 --> 01:37:19,012
Oh, hi.

1116
01:37:19,390 --> 01:37:21,224
You'll be all right.

1117
01:37:21,725 --> 01:37:25,228
Boy, the superintendent's gonna be pissed.

1118
01:37:26,729 --> 01:37:28,648
Are you okay?

1119
01:37:29,315 --> 01:37:31,192
Who are you guys?

1120
01:37:31,359 --> 01:37:33,403
We're the Ghostbusters.

1121
01:37:36,239 --> 01:37:37,657
Who does your taxes?

1122
01:37:38,408 --> 01:37:41,536
You know, Mr. Tully, you are a most fortunate individual.

1123
01:37:41,703 --> 01:37:43,997
- I know. - You have been a participant in...

1124
01:37:44,164 --> 01:37:47,750
...the biggest interdimensional cross rip since the Tunguska blast of 1909.

1125
01:37:47,917 --> 01:37:50,086
- Felt great. - We'd like to get a sample...

1126
01:37:50,253 --> 01:37:53,131
...of your brain tissue. - Okay.

1127
01:37:56,176 --> 01:37:58,886
I love this town!

1128
01:38:42,722 --> 01:38:44,724
Egon!

1129
01:38:51,689 --> 01:38:53,608
What's going on?

1130
01:38:54,652 --> 01:38:56,985
Does anybody want to interview me?

1131
01:38:57,195 --> 01:39:00,573
I'm an eyewitness. I was up there.

1132
01:39:01,115 --> 01:39:03,283
I want to go with them in the car.

